  <description><![CDATA[<p>Giotto Hotel &amp; Spa boasts a fantastic location in the centre of Assisi, overlooking the Umbrian Valley. The Medieval town makes for a spectacular backdrop to the hotel and there’s plenty to explore in St. Francis’ birthplace like the Basilica di Santa Chiara. The town is even more enchanting in the evening when the day-trippers have left and you’ll be pleased to be within walking distance of plenty of authentic restaurants.</p>
<p>The hotel itself has been elegantly furnished and has grand hallways, charming guestrooms and more than 1500 square metres of terraces that allow you to appreciate the panoramic views from its hillside setting. The restaurant is the perfect place to enjoy a leisurely meal, made using local ingredients, and watch the sun set over the valley. There’s also a wine cellar with some of Umbria’s best labels, and a coffee shop and bar. Those looking to relax will appreciate the hotel’s spa (payable locally).</p>]]></description>
